    "body": "Thanks, looks like it will get me moving.\n\nHowever, doing things this way does mean you also need to know the location of the ipython config folder, which might customized by a user or python distro - it would be nice if either the json you mentioned or the config location was available by \"asking\" the ipython process. \n\nI notice also that there are JSON files for running kernels, but in my instance at least there is a bunch of jsons for old kernels (i suspect ones that I had to force-shutdown). Might a seperate issue but it would probably be good for ipython to clean up defunct JSON files on startup...\n"
